{"title_page": "List of public art in Powys", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n[[File:Wales Powys locator map.svg|thumb|Map of Wales with Powys highlighted]]\nThis is a '''list of public art in [[Powys]]''', Wales. This list applies only to works of [[public art]] on permanent display in an outdoor public space and does not, for example, include artworks in museums.\n\n==Brecon==\n{{Public art header|show_architect=no|show_material=yes|show_dimensions=yes|show_owner=no|show_wikidata=yes}}\n{{Public art row\n| image = The Duke of Wellington - geograph.org.uk - 4247541.jpg\n| commonscat = Statue of the Duke of Wellington, Brecon\n| subject = [[Arthur Wellesley, 1st Duke of Wellington|Duke of Wellington]] Monument\n| location = The Bulwark, [[Brecon]]\n| date = 1852\n| show_artist= yes\n| artist = [[John Evan Thomas]]\n| type = Statue\n| material = Bronze statue on stone pedestal\n| dimensions = Statue 2.5m high\n| designation = Grade II \n| coordinates =\n| show_wikidata= yes\n| wikidata = Q28087861\n| notes = <ref name=\"Duke\">{{cadw |num=6838 |desc=The Duke of Wellington monument |accessdate= 23 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Pevsner\"/>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image = War Memorial - St Mary&#039;s Church \u2013 Bulwark - geograph.org.uk - 3457874.jpg\n| commonscat =\n| subject = War memorial\n| location = Grounds of St Mary's Church, [[Brecon]] \n| date = 1920\n| show_artist= \n| artist = \n| type = Celtic cross\n| material = Stone\n| dimensions = 2m high\n| designation = \n| coordinates=\n| show_wikidata= yes\n| wikidata =\n| notes = <ref name=HPbwm>{{cite web |author=|url=https://historypoints.org/index.php?page=brecon-war-memorial|title=Brecon war memorial|date=|accessdate=26 January 2020|work=historypoints.org}}</ref><ref name=\"IWMbc\">{{cite web |author=|url=https://www.iwm.org.uk/memorials/item/memorial/6835  |title=War Memorials Register: Brecon Cros