rial Fountain |accessdate=27 January 2020}}</ref> \n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image = \n| commonscat =\n| subject = War memorial\n| location = [[Llangynidr]] Parish Church, [[Crickhowell]]\n| date = 1920\n| show_artist= \n| artist = \n| type = Celtic cross\n| material = Stone\n| dimensions =\n| designation = \n| coordinates=\n| show_wikidata= yes\n| wikidata =\n| notes = <ref name=\"IWMchl\">{{cite web |author=|url=https://www.iwm.org.uk/memorials/item/memorial/75165  |title=War Memorials Register: Llangynidr |date= |accessdate=26 January 2020|work= Imperial War Museum}}</ref> \n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image = Crickhowell War Memorial - geograph.org.uk - 4283646.jpg\n| commonscat =\n| subject = War memorial\n| location = Beaufort St., [[Crickhowell]]\n| date = \n| show_artist= \n| artist = \n| type = Monolith\n| material = Granite\n| dimensions = 3m high\n| designation = \n| coordinates=\n| show_wikidata= yes\n| wikidata =\n| notes = Marks the site of a demolished memorial hospital.<ref>{{cite web |author=|url=https://www.iwm.org.uk/memorials/item/memorial/6842  |title=War Memorials Register: Crickhowell and District Memorial Hospital |date= |accessdate=7 January 2020|work= Imperial War Museum}}</ref> \n}}\n{{Public art footer}}\n\n==Criggion==\n{{Public art header|show_architect=no|show_material=yes|show_dimensions=yes|show_owner=no|show_wikidata=yes}}\n{{Public art row\n| image = Rodney&#039;s Pillar - geograph.org.uk - 1138443.jpg\n| commonscat = Rodney's Pillar\n| subject = [[George Brydges Rodney, 1st Baron Rodney|Admiral Rodney's]] Pillar\n| location = [[Breidden Hill]] near [[Criggion]]\n| date = 1781\u201382\n| show_artist= \n| artist = \n| type = Doric column\n| material = Stone\n| dimensions =\n| designation = Grade II*\n| coordinates=\n| show_wikidata= yes\n| wikidata =\n| notes = <ref>{{cadw|num=7667 |desc= Rodney's Pillar |accessdate=23 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Pevsner\">{{cite book|author=Robert Scourfield & Richard Haslam|publisher=Yale Universit