-Wye]]\n| date = 1922, repositioned 1950\n| show_artist= \n| artist = \n| type = Tapered cross on pedestal and stepped plinth\n| material = Stone\n| dimensions = \n| designation = \n| coordinates = \n| show_wikidata= yes\n| wikidata = \n| notes =<ref>{{cite web |author=|url=https://historypoints.org/index.php?page=hay-on-wye-war-memorial |title= Hay-on-Wye war memorials|date=|accessdate=7 February 2020|work=historypoints.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=|url=https://www.iwm.org.uk/memorials/item/memorial/6843|title=War Memorials Register: Hay and Cusop |date= |accessdate=7 February 2020|work= Imperial War Museum}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Public art footer}}\n\n==Knighton==\n{{Public art header|show_architect=no|show_material=yes|show_dimensions=yes|show_owner=no|show_wikidata=yes}}\n{{Public art row\n| image = Knighton War Memorial (1), Brookside Square, Knighton, Powys - geograph.org.uk - 3190176.jpg\n| commonscat = \n| subject = War memorial \n| location = [[Knighton, Powys|Knighton]]\n| date = 1921, moved & rededicated 1980\n| show_artist= \n| artist = \n| type = Cenotaph\n| material = Granite\n| dimensions = 6m tall\n| designation = \n| coordinates = \n| show_wikidata= yes\n| wikidata = \n| notes = <ref>{{cite web |author=|url=https://www.iwm.org.uk/memorials/item/memorial/37273|title=War Memorials Register: Knighton Cenotaph |date= |accessdate=6 February 2020|work= Imperial War Museum}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Public art footer}}\n\n==Llandinam==\n{{Public art header|show_architect=no|show_material=yes|show_dimensions=yes|show_owner=no|show_wikidata=yes}}\n{{Public art row\n| image = David Davies Llandinam - geograph.org.uk - 1389119.jpg \n| commonscat = \n| subject = [[David Davies (industrialist)|David Davies]], 1818\u20131890\n| location = Near to Llandinam Bridge, [[Llandinam]] \n| date = 1893\n| show_artist= yes\n| artist = [[Alfred Gilbert]]\n| type = Statue\n| material = Bronze statue on a limestone plinth\n| dimensions =\n| designation = Grade II*\n| coordinates =\n| show_