ple of Ulster-Scottish descent]]\n[[Category:Great Northern Railway (U.S.)]]\n[[Category:Spokane, Portland and Seattle Railway]]\n[[Category:Northern Pacific Railway people]]\n[[Category:Chicago, Burlington and Quincy Railroad people]]\n[[Category:Persons of National Historic Significance (Canada)]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Saint Paul, Minnesota]]\n[[Category:Minnesota Democrats]]\n", "name_user": "All Hallow's Wraith", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_J._Hill"}
{"title_page": "Learning through Landscapes", "text_new": "{{Infobox non-profit\n| name              = Learning through Landscapes\n| image             = \n| type              = Children's Charity\n| founded_date      = 1990<ref>[http://www.ltl.org.uk/about-us]</ref>\n| tax_id            =\n| registration_id   =\n| founder           =\n| location          =\n| origins           =\n| key_people        =\n| area_served       =\n| product           =\n| mission           =\n| focus             =\n| method            =\n| revenue           =\n| endowment         =\n| num_volunteers    =\n| num_employees     =\n| num_members       =\n| subsid            =\n| owner             =\n| non-profit_slogan = Inspiring outdoor learning and play.\n| former name       =\n| homepage          ={{url|www.ltl.org.uk/}}\n| dissolved         =\n| footnotes         =\n}}\n\n'''Learning through Landscapes''' (LtL) is a UK [[Charity organization|charity]] which promotes children's outdoor learning and play through improved use of school playgrounds. Started in 1990 as the output of a research project, the charity soon grew in response to the demand from schools and funders.\n\nLtL was a founding partner of  the Scottish 'Grounds for Learning Project' funded by [[Scottish Natural Heritage]]. Scottish Natural Heritage has remained a main partner of LtL in Scotland for 25 years. Grounds for Learning was re-named 'LtL Scotland' in 2019 and maintains an office in [[Stirling]].\n\nLearning through Landscapes has been involved with a number of projects including: Local School Nature Grants (in partnership with Peoples Postcode Lottery)ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ltl.org.uk/projects/local-school-nature-grants/ |title=Local School Nature Grants |publisher=LtL |date= |accessdate=2017-03-07}}</ref>, Outdoor Classroom Day (UK & Ireland) {{url|https://www.ltl.org.uk/projects/outdoor-classroom-day/}}, Living through Landscapes (dementia friendly gardens) {{url|https://www.ltl.org.uk/projects/living-through-landscapes/}}, Woodland Play {{url|https://www.ltl.org.uk/projects/woodland-play/}}  The Scottish Natural Play project, Fruitfull Schools {{url|https://www.ltl.org.uk/projects/fruit-full-schools/}}, Fruitful Communities {{url|https://www.ltl.org.uk/projects/fruit-full-communities/}} and Polli:Nation {{url|https://www.ltl.org.uk/projects/pollination/}}. \n\nLtL offers many free outdoor lesson ideas {{url|https://www.ltl.org.uk/free-resources/}}, outdoor learning training and advice. It operates from two offices, one in Winchester and one in Stirling.\n\nThe charity has been involved in many publications on behalf of local and national government, notably in School Grounds Design for DfEE {{url|https://www.ltl.org.uk/resources/school-grounds-design-guide/}} and The Good School Playground Guide for the Scottish Government {{url|https://www.ltl.org.uk/resources/the-good-school-playground-guide/}}.\n\nLtL was one of the founder members of the International School Grounds Alliance {{url|http://www.internationalschoolgrounds.org/}} having hosted the first International School Grounds conference in Hampshire in 2010.\n\nIts patrons are: \n[[Sir David Attenborough]], who in 2014 created their Basic Need film,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ImZhcNIL07s|title=Basic need &#124; Learning through Landscapes |website=Ltl.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2017-03-07}}</ref> this refers to the basic shortage of school places currently being experienced by schools.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20150518081654/http://www.london.gov.uk/media/assembly-press-releases/2013/09/london-s-school-place-shortage ]</ref>\n\n[[Jonathon Porritt]] and Lord Remnant CVO FCA\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://ltl.org.uk Official website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20111223225855/http://greenschoolyards.org/blog/entry/2135593/interview-with-mary-jackson-learning-through-landscapes International School Grounds Alliance]\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Learning Through Landscapes}}\n[[Category:Charities based in Hampshire]]\n[[Category:Children's charities based in the United Kingdom]]\n\n\n{{philanthropy-org-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox non-profit\n| name              = Learning through Landscapes\n| image             = \n| type              = Children's Charity\n| founded_date      = 1990<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070507044546/http://www.ltl.org.uk/about-us.htm]</ref>\n| tax_id            =\n| registration_id   =\n| founder           =\n| location          =\n| origins           =\n| key_people        =\n| area_served       =\n| product           =\n| mission           =\n| focus             =\n| method            =\n| revenue           =\n| endowment         =\n| num_volunteers    =\n| num_employees     =\n| num_members       =\n| subsid            =\n| owner             =\n| non-profit_slogan = Inspiring outdoor learning and play.\n| former name       =\n| homepage          ={{url|ltl.org.uk/}}\n| dissolved         =\n| footnotes         =\n}}\n\n'''Learning through Landscapes''' (LTL) is a UK [[Charity organization|charity]] which promotes children's outdoor activities through improved use of school playgrounds.\n\nLearning through Landscapes has been involved with a number of projects including: Supergrounds,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ltl.org.uk/spaces/corporate-casestudy.php |title=Case study: RBS Supergrounds &#124; Learning through Landscapes |website=Ltl.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2017-03-07}}</ref> The Scottish Play project<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.playscotland.org/resources/play-in-schools/ |title=Play in Schools |publisher=Play Scotland |date= |accessdate=2017-03-07}}</ref> and Polli:Nation <ref>{{cite web|url=https://buglife.org.uk/tags/pollination-0 |title=Polli:Nation |publisher=Buglife |date=2015-02-13 |accessdate=2017-03-07}}</ref>  These projects are funded from both grants and membership.\n\nIts patron is [[Sir David Attenborough]], who in 2014 created their Basic Need film,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ltl.org.uk/basicneed/ |title=Basic need &#124; Learning through Landscapes |website=Ltl.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2017-03-07}}</ref> this refers to the basic shortage of school places currently being experienced by schools.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20150518081654/http://www.london.gov.uk/media/assembly-press-releases/2013/09/london-s-school-place-shortage ]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://ltl.org.uk Official website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20111223225855/http://greenschoolyards.org/blog/entry/2135593/interview-with-mary-jackson-learning-through-landscapes International School Grounds Alliance]\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Learning Through Landscapes}}\n[[Category:Charities based in Hampshire]]\n[[Category:Children's charities based in the United Kingdom]]\n\n\n{{philanthropy-org-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Matt outandabout", "label": "safe", "comment": "Updated current programmes and links as the weblinks were broken.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Learning_through_Landscapes"}
